---
title: Double Mediterranean Fish & Roast Pumpkin Salad with Greens & Balsamic Dressing
description: Dishes from the Mediterranean are known for being fresh and light, so let’s take a page out of their recipe book and add it to our own archive. Cook up fish in a garlic and herb seasoning, served on top of a roast pumpkin salad, speckled with pumpkin seeds and drizzled in a balsamic and olive oil dressing.

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving and under 30g carbohydrates per serving.*

